## Harmony Principles

  P1: Accent temperature should match or be neutral to base
  P2: Colors with semantic meaning must not be adjacent or competing
  P3: Same color family requires 400+ step difference
  P4: One temperature must dominate; other is accent only
  P5: Semantic meaning ALWAYS takes precedence over temperature harmony

## Forbidden Patterns [5]

  - Same family on itself: Insufficient contrast, colors blend
  - Raw hex colors: Breaks themes, not maintainable
  - Standard Tailwind colors: Not DDS tokens, inconsistent
  - Opacity on semantic tokens: Use glass patterns or solid tokens
  - Text on low-opacity glass without backdrop: Text unreadable on varied backgrounds

## Glass Depths

  depth1: opacity=60% blur=8px (direct text OK)
  depth2: opacity=40% blur=4px (semantic or nested)
  depth3: opacity=20% blur=2px (nested solid required)
  minOpacityForDirectText: 60%
  nestedGlass: FORBIDDEN - use solid bg-surface inside glass containers

## Color Families [11]

  ABYSS: neutral-cool - Dark theme base
  DEEP_CURRENT: cool (brand) - Primary accent, CTAs, links
  WAVE: cool (info) - Info states, secondary teal accent
  HARBOR: cool (success) - Success states, confirmations
  CORAL: warm (error) - Error states, destructive actions
  SUNRISE: warm (warning) - Warning states, caution
  ORANGE: warm (highlight) - Energy, attention, badges
  SLATE: neutral - Universal gray, borders, muted text
  LINEN: cool - Cool blue-white scale, subtle cool tints
  IVORY: neutral-warm - Light theme depth layering (page/surface/elevated)
  DUSK_REEF: neutral-cool - Sophisticated neutral, secondary text

## Escape Hatch

  attribute: data-dds-override
  usage: Add to element when intentionally breaking rules

## Composite Rules

  valid: modal > card, card > surface, page > card
  forbidden: glass > glass, surface > card, badge > badge
  rule: When in doubt: inner element's context rules apply for colors/borders; outer element provides only background/backdrop